[The report is intriguing as it suggest exposure in a very high risk area.
The most obvious place of infection is in East Africa which, however, is
difficult to prove. The cases shows that a malaria blood slide examined by
a competent microscopists is part of the routine examination of febrile
patients even in cases where it is not obvious that the patient has been
exposed to malaria. - Mod.EP
